Successfully reproduced bug `5aec788aeb8e` (sched: Fix TASK_state comparisons):

- **Driver**: `kmod/drivers/task_state_cmp.c`
- **Bug**: `___wait_is_interruptible(TASK_INTERRUPTIBLE|TASK_FREEZABLE)` uses equality (`==`) instead of bitmask (`&`), returning false. This causes `wait_event_freezable()` to ignore signals and spin indefinitely.
- **Buggy kernel**: `fail` — kthread stuck in TASK_RUNNING (busy-loop)
- **Fixed kernel**: `pass` — kthread correctly exits wait on signal
- **Committed & pushed** ✅


